                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="arcadian_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">of or connected with Arcadia or an idea of perfect country life</span></span><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="arcadian_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">late 16th cent.: from Latin <span class="ei">Arcadius</span>, from Greek <span class="ei">Arkadia</span>. Arcadia is literally a mountainous district in the Peloponnese of southern Greece. It represents a pastoral paradise in poetic fantasy and is the home of Pan in Greek mythology.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
